## units
- pt, px, ex, em, rem, %, pica
- output media : screen or paper
- absolute units : 1in = 2.54cm = 25.4mm = 72pt = 6pc
- relative units : em
- units depend on the font : em, ex 

# recommended units
- screen : em, px, %
- print : em, cm, mm, in, pt, pc, %



# pt, 

# point
- typographic unit
- in typography, the point is the smallest unit of measure. 
- DTP point,DeskTop Publishing point
- DTP point is defined as 1/72 of an international inch

# pica
- typographic unit
- The pica is a typographic unit of measure corresponding to approximately 1/6 of an inch, or from 1/68 to 1/73 of a foot. One pica is further divided into 12 points.

# DPI,Dots per Inch


